cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is about using machine learning models to personalize web search results based on user and query contexts. Therefore, the most likely category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses neural net and tree-based learning-to-rank and regression models, which are common in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions using natural language processing techniques to extract features from user queries, which falls under Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of context to improve search results, which could be relevant to Cybersecurity (cs.CY) in terms of identifying and mitigating potential security threats.
